<item>
            <title>[SPARK-28163] Kafka ignores user configuration on FETCH_OFFSET_NUM_RETRY and FETCH_OFFSET_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28163</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are &quot;unsafe&quot; conversions in the Kafka connector.&lt;br/&gt;
CaseInsensitiveStringMap comes in which is then converted the following way:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
...
options.asScala.toMap
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main problem with this is that such case it looses its case insensitive nature&lt;br/&gt;
(case insensitive map is converting the key to lower case when get/contains called).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
